    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How should I store Japanese gummies?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Store Japanese gummies in a cool, dry place below 77°F (25°C). Because many Japanese gummies have higher fruit juice content and fewer preservatives than American candy, they can become sticky or lose texture in heat. Resealable bags should be pressed flat to remove air. In hot climates, refrigeration preserves texture without affecting flavor. Most Japanese gummies have a shelf life of 6-12 months from production.' },
