<div class="pcard-specs">
          <div class="pcard-spec"><strong>Juice Content</strong><span>15% concentrated fruit juice</span></div>
          <div class="pcard-spec"><strong>Top Flavors</strong><span>Strawberry, green apple, grape, mango</span></div>
          <div class="pcard-spec"><strong>Texture</strong><span>Chewy-taffy hybrid, multi-layered</span></div>
          <div class="pcard-spec"><strong>Origin</strong><span>Morinaga & Company, Tokyo, Japan</span></div>
        </div>
<div class="pcard-pros-cons">
          <div class="pcard-pros">
            <h4>Pros</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Most widely available Japanese candy in the US — sold at Walmart, Target, CVS</li>
              <li>Unique chewy-taffy texture unlike any American gummy</li>
              <li>Huge flavor variety — 20+ flavors including seasonal limited editions</li>
              <li>Excellent value with large bags available under $5</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="pcard-cons">
            <h4>Cons</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>US formulation differs slightly from Japanese-market version</li>
              <li>Sticks to dental work — not ideal for people with fillings or braces</li>
              <li>Lower fruit juice content than Kasugai or Meiji</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pcard-ctas">
          <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=Hi-Chew+japanese+gummy+candy&tag=gummyguidepro-20" class="btn-cta" target="_blank" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener">Check Price on Amazon</a>
        </div>
